main event: The report is about an unidentified flying object sighting in Peck, Montana on July 15, 1950 by a pilot and crew at 13,000 feet for 12 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting took place at 13,000 feet and lasted for 12 minutes, indicating a prolonged and detailed observation.
The object was reported as circular and flying in a group about 3,000 feet below the observer's aircraft.
The document is heavily redacted, suggesting a high level of secrecy and classified information related to the UFO sighting.
The report is from Project Blue Book, which was a U.S. Air Force program for the investigation of UFO reports.
The sighting involved not only the pilot but also the crew, adding credibility to the observation.
